<plot>Following the movements of ten people from different social and cultural backgrounds in São Paulo, the filmmaker redraws the map of South America's largest metropolis. It is the railway tracks, the taxi routes and the underground lines that both structure the city and reveal its rhythm, its daily rituals and the diversity of cultures that live within it.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?615764</url></doc>
